metadata.name: Emotional Shell #351
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 72 · 54 · 40 · 30 · 24 · 20 every 8 minutes.
Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted, and then drop one price tier.

---------

The feeling of being human – with all of its intricate hopes, struggles, and fleeting emotions – seems so unique that we assume artificial intelligence could never replicate our experience. And while we devise systems for solving unfathomably complex problems, generating algorithmic creativity, and unlocking regenerative biological possibilities, we simultaneously cling to the power and originality of emotional feeling – believing it to be the irreplaceable source of what makes us human.

If the body is our shell for emotion and soul, can an artificial humanoid be another vessel for these thoughts and feelings – for human essence itself? If our ‘soul’ is the last stand between us and the machines, what happens when the soul becomes transferable? That we may see answers to these questions looks more real every year, and is perhaps a little frightening. 

Emotional Shell uses introspective portraits of future selves to question what it means to be human, when the people around us are no longer human.

---------

Warning: This piece is GPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices.

Press 'S' to save the image at the current scale
Press 'H' to save the image at 2400px resolution

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #1209
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

metadata.name: Daydreamer #186
metadata.description:
‘For the artist communication with nature remains the most essential condition. The artist is human, himself nature; part of nature within natural space.’ (Paul Klee, 1944) 


Working on long-form nature has an interesting side effect. On the one hand, you're attempting a shallow imitation of a landscape.... You are working with cold logic and code, vainly trying to control randomness to create this virtual facsimile, something you know is artificial.... 

....and yet.... even with all this left-brain activity, your right-brain pushes back, and imagines being there. While working on this project I found myself continually daydreaming, wandering off to hear the sounds of waterfalls, or the crunch of walking along a sandy lake shore. If you've ever wondered about coding, I urge you to learn. Daydreams await....


Press '1' once rendering is finished, to redraw at 5120x5120 resolution 
Press '2' to export without post-processing effects 

3rd party libraries (license text and links included in source) 
- p5.js - Creative coding framework 
- JS Topology Suite "JSTS", a port of Java Topology Suite "JTS" - High-level Geometry library 
- WebGLImageFilter, Dominic Szablewski - phoboslab.org 

I have tried to use soft blurs and shadows to give a sense of layering and depth to the scene. After viewing for a while, it reminds me of 3D paper-art. There are traits for colour and amount of birds, waterfalls, etc. but none are especially rare – These properties are intended for filtering the collection.

metadata.name: Qualia #38
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

'Qualia' are personal instances of conscious experience; for example what it 'feels' like to see a color, or a shape.

Each image in this project is designed to provoke a personal experience of color and form.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x1500px PNG.

metadata.name: Pixelnetika #23
metadata.description:
-------------------------------------------------

'drop it like it's raw'

-------------------------------------------------
Mouse-click switches between:
- screen scaled image
- The large image - with finer details

right-click: save/copy image

A custom created 'soft' pixel 2D/3D engine 
written in vanilla JavaScript
some more info in the source-code
The work will refresh and restart after some time
-------------------------------------------------

Pixelnetika - magnetic storms - Raw sketch 

-------------------------------------------------
Seen it in the past, whenever a group comes together.
Graffiti scene / Demo scene / Art scene etc. etc. 
New rules start popping up,
you should do this, you should do that..
Can't do this do this, you should not do that.
New rules, that can hinder you. 
If you start conforming/obeying the rules

Like seen people, making lovely works,
'but it should have more variations'
Adding all kinds of extras, 
that only made the work 
less powerful in the end

Or loosing themselves 
in the small details

Making 100 great and lovely sketches,
and finally releasing a work 
that totally did not work or sell at all.

Such a shame.


Well, it does not have enough variations

Variations: != 100 different extras?

For example, look at the Mark's Smoll-skulls or like Casey Reas works,
or like 100 warhol soup-cans, all just a littlebit different

I knew a classic composer, 
that really enjoyed creating works
when he was young.
Became a teacher,
conform within the institution
And lost all the joy he had for composing,
due to pressure and rules 'how things should be done'


Don't post too much

Some people like to work on 1 painting for years
trying to create their own Mona Lisa.

While Vincent van Gogh would paint lightning fast,
sometimes doing 1 painting a day


Break the rules
Make your own rules
set yourself free.
-------------------------------------------------

xxx Amsterdam chillout

For the love of Art, Polar bears, and throwing snowballs ^__^

August 12 2022

metadata.name: Plottable Memories: Train Station #59
metadata.description:
'Memories: Train Station' explores plottable abstract photography composition around the "Train Station" theme. Memories can be blurry, faded and abstract and the strokes texturing aim to reflect that.

Many images are used as primitive to make the plot texture. The work is very generative and have great range of variety thanks to the many effects combined together. Photos has been taken by @greweb in Paris' "Gare de l'Est" train station.

Traits of the art includes a suggested "Title" that is self-generated.

PLOTTABLE?!

A SVG file can be exported (right click save) to plot the piece physically. The plot is made of up to 200 000 points – making it time consuming to produce. It is recommended to optimize the pen travel. Inks can have surprising outcomes when done physically.

The digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece, owning it confers the right to plot or request a physical plot from @greweb (https://greweb.me/plots/nft). @greweb would use fountain pens but other plotting artists are free to achieve it with their own materials and ship to collectors – as long as NFT is owned at request time.

More details and Source code: https://github.com/gre/gre/tree/master/doodles/plottable-memories-train-station

@greweb – 2022 – tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM – CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: (Un)typed #91
metadata.description:
"(Un)typed" is an exploration to achieve composition and harmony by means of typed letters and symbols. Untyped letters are just as valuable as typed letters, so blanks and filled spaces are equally valuable. The selected color palettes have high color contrast and harmony, and their different combinations make each work unique.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.

metadata.name: Chop Chop #150
metadata.description:
Chop Chop is a complementary collection to Caterpillars that I prepared to thank my collectors for the amazing love and interest you showed to my work. I did not want to force my way to your wallets with unsolicited thank-you nfts, so all holders of Caterpillars will have a reserve spot to mint at least 1 tokens per wallet for 0 tez ( I dont understand the reserve options fully, sorry - 128 editions reserved for holders of Caterpillars) . 

The holders of this collection will have reserve spots for my next  collection. The reserve spots will be held for one week from minting, and I prefer the unreserved editions to be fair game for anyone, so first come, first served.

I decided to re-work this older project of mine because it was going to take some time for me to prepare an independent and novel collection and also wanted to continue learning new things. The concept is Paul Klee meets Vector Math and Flow Fields, as you can see the visuals are heavily inspired by Paul Klee's work :)

Under the hood, the circles and triangles act as repulsive forces that break and distort the grid, and push the squares in their range out of their way, forming some holes in the fabric created by the same algo that made Caterpillars. 

I have only added one rarity feature which is the palette because this one uses almost all the palettes from Caterpillars (minus neon dreams). I am hoping that this project will not be about rarity, but more like a thank-you gift and an easy way to access my future work.

Well, I hope you will like it...

- Press "s" to save a png.

- Also, 33% royalty split wth the Processing Foundation, % 33 with the minters (if there will be any secondary sales) 

DISCLAIMER :
I am very very new to coding and not very good at this. I have tried to clean up the code as best as I could, and I hope that there is nothing terribly wrong left inside.
